---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import ProjectPageHeader from '../../components/ProjectPageHeader.astro';
import ProjectSection from '../../components/ProjectSection.astro';
import ProjectList from '../../components/ProjectList.astro';
import ProjectProse from '../../components/ProjectProse.astro';
import TagList from '../../components/TagList.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro';
---

<Base title="Pularis / Kacper Noniewicz" description="Stateless Go polling adapter for HTTP APIs.">
  <div class="py-16 pb-20">
    <ProjectPageHeader label="Public / Go / MIT" title="Pularis" intro="A small Go service that polls HTTP APIs on a schedule, transforms the responses into structured events, and publishes them to Redis. It owns no storage and no state." repo="https://github.com/knoniewicz/pularis" />

    <div class="max-w-180">
      <ProjectSection title="What it does">
        <ProjectList items={[
          "Polls HTTP endpoints at configurable intervals",
          "Extracts fields from JSON responses using gjson paths",
          "Conditionally publishes events based on expr rules",
          "Tracks session transitions automatically (created/ended)",
          "Emits events to Redis channels for downstream consumers",
        ]} />
      </ProjectSection>

      <ProjectSection title="Why I built it">
        <ProjectProse>
          <p>I kept writing the same adapter code for every new API I wanted to ingest: polling loop, auth wiring, JSON extraction, event publishing. Pularis turns that into configuration. You write a TOML file describing the source, and Pularis handles the rest.</p>
        </ProjectProse>
      </ProjectSection>

      <ProjectSection title="How it works">
        <CodeBlock>name = "example_source"
endpoint = "https://api.example.com/status"
poll_interval_seconds = 15

[[events]]
name = "activity"
is_session = true
on_changed_fields = ["state"]
publish_when = "state != ''"

[events.transform]
user_id = "data.user.id"
state = "data.session.state"</CodeBlock>
        <ProjectProse>
          <p>Auth credentials live in a companion <code class="font-mono text-sm">.auth.json</code> file next to the TOML config. Header values reference auth keys with placeholders.</p>
        </ProjectProse>
      </ProjectSection>

      <ProjectSection title="Stack">
        <TagList tags={["Go", "Redis", "gjson", "expr"]} />
      </ProjectSection>

      <ProjectSection title="Status">
        <ProjectProse>
          <p>Public and usable. I run it as part of my personal infrastructure to ingest data from several external APIs. MIT licensed.</p>
        </ProjectProse>
      </ProjectSection>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
